         <div type="commentary">
            <head>Commentary</head>
            <p>The style of the mosaic seems post-Hadrianic but earlier than the Byzantine reconstruction of the building.  See M. Luni and G. Cellini, 
                'L'Abside della Basilica nel foro di Cirene', <title>Karthago</title> 24 (1999), 27-73, who point out (p.34) that a figure of justice 
                is entirely appropriate to the functions of the building.</p>
            <p>In the wall immediately above the panel is a niche which contained, when excavated, the lower part of a statue of a woman accompanied 
                    by a winged creature - presumably Nemesis accompanied by a gryphon (see 
                  Paribeni, 1959, 424)</p>
         </div>
         
